            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Igitur fidelium nostrorum presentium ac futurorum noverit multitudo. Quoniam
                            <rs key="#Intercessory">per interventum</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #childOf" ref="#people/3042"
                            >Robberti</persName> nostri dilectissimi <rs key="#childOf">filii</rs>
                        ac <persName key="#Intercessory #Other_palatine_officer #fidelisOf"
                            ref="#people/3035">Odoaldi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">camerarii</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #fidelisOf" ref="#people/4265">Mansonis</persName>
                        nostrorum dilectorum <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelium</rs>, necnon ob salutem
                        et remedium animarum quondam <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis"
                            >gloriosorum</rs> principum videlicet <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #grandparentOf"
                            ref="#people/3001">Richardi primi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">principis</rs>
                        <rs key="#grandparentOf">avi</rs>, ac bone memorie <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #parentOf" ref="#people/3002"
                            >Iordani</persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">patris</rs> atque<persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #siblingOf"
                            ref="#people/3010"> secundi Richardi</persName> quam et <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #siblingOf"
                            ref="#people/3019">Robberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">principum</rs>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">fratrum</rs> nostrorum, et ob statum nostri
                        principatus. Per hoc videlicet principale scriptum in perpetuum damus,
                        tradimus, concedimus ac confirmamus <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterio</rs><orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3046"> Sancti Angeli quod dicitur in
                            Formis</orgName> in quo domnus <persName key="#Prevosts #Personal_rank"
                            ref="#people/4266">Maurus</persName> Dei gratia <rs key="#Personal_rank"
                            >venerabilis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs> preesse dinoscitur, scilicet hunc
                        subscriptum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">hominem</rs>
                        <rs key="#Public_exactions">cum omnibus rebus et substantiis ipsius</rs> ut
                        ipse faciat et persolvat predicto monasterio Sancti Angeli et iam dicto
                        domno Mauro venerabili preposito suisque successoribus semper<rs
                            key="#Census"> censum </rs>et <rs key="#Datium">dationem</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Public_exactions">publicalia et scaditionem</rs> et alia omnia que
                        parti publice facere aut persolvere debet aut debuerit. Nomen cuius hoc est,
                        videlicet <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #childOf"><name
                                ref="Symeon Caprarius">Simeon cognomento Caprarius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs> quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes Benerosi">Iohannis Benerosi</name></persName> qui est
                        habitator in loco qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/5463">li Benerosi
                        </placeName>non multum longe a prefato monasterio Sancti Angeli. Remota omni
                        inquietudine, contrarietate vel molestia omnium principum successorum
                        nostrorum vel vice principum, comitum vel vice comitum, iudicum, sculdaorum,
                        castaldeorum aliorumque omnium mortalium persone. Quod si quis huius nostre
                        dationis, traditionis, concessionis atque confirmationis pagine contemptor
                        aut violator extiterit, aut contra hoc principale scriptum hagere
                        temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">decem librarum auri purissimi</rs>
                        persolvat, medietatem predicto monasterio Sancti Angeli et iam dicto domno
                        Mauro venerabili preposito eiusque successoribus, et medietatem nostro sacro
                        palatio. Solutaque pena librarum auri, hoc principale scriptum firmum,
                        munitum atque inviolabile maneat in perpetuum. Et ut hoc principale scriptum
                        firmius credatur et diligentius ab omnibus observetur, manu propria illud
                        corroboravimus, et nostri sigilli illud insigniri iussimus. (M) Ex iussione
                        prephate serenissime potestatis, scripsi ego <persName key="#Writer #Judge"
                            ref="#people/3037">Philippus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">palatinus iudex</rs>. In anno dominice incarnationis M° C°
                        XX° III°; et tertio anno principatus predicti domni <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis" ref="#people/3022"
                            >Iordani</persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">gloriosi</rs>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">principis</rs> Capue. Data <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/173">Capue</placeName> in mense abrelis, per indictionem
                        primam. </ab>
